# Architecture

## Stack

Next.js 15 App Router + TypeScript + Tailwind + Shadcn + Supabase + Stripe + Mux + Vercel + Resend.

**No Express.** No Shopify. No separate backend repo.

## Modular Monolith

One repo, feature-based folders:

- `src/app/` — routes and API handlers only
- `src/features/` — domain modules
- `src/server/` — services, actions, webhooks, jobs
- `src/lib/` — provider clients and shared utilities
- `components/` — reusable presentation

## Source of Truth

| Domain | Owner |
|--------|-------|
| Payments | Stripe (webhooks sync local DB) |
| App data & access | Supabase PostgreSQL |
| Video streaming | Mux (signed playback) |
| UX & orchestration | Next.js |

## Key Rules

- Entitlement checks live in `server/services/entitlementService` — never hardcode plan access in UI.
- Grant subscription/product access **after webhook**, not checkout redirect.
- Webhooks: verify signature → store event → idempotent process.
- GHL/email failures: log + retry; never block user flows.
- Background jobs: `integration_jobs` + Vercel Cron (no queue service in MVP).

## Feature Boundaries

Each feature owns its domain only:

- `auth` — login/signup/session; not entitlements
- `billing` — Stripe checkout/portal/webhooks; not UI styling
- `video` — Mux tokens/upload; not progress logic
- `progress` — watch state; not certificate issuance directly
- `integrations` — GHL, Resend, Calendly; isolated in `server/integrations/`

## Do Not Build in MVP

Native apps, offline downloads, full DRM, community forum, custom scheduling, affiliate system, microservices.
